This file is just my understandings on GIT commands and its usage.These commands are executed in GIT_BASH.exe

Git init -                                            Creates the repository in the local machine.Its default location for creating a repo is the C Drive.In some machines it ll throw us the Permission denied exception.

To Overcome Permission denied exception , use the below command. 
Git init /D(Drive_Name)/Folder_Name/Repository_Name - Command creates a Repository in the user desiered location.

Git Help -                                            Gives info about the commands that we use in git and its description.

Cd ~ -                                                Points to the local Repository.

cd /f(User Specified Path) -                          Points to the desired path of the user.
